Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "zadužen" in different forms and positions with translations in English in parentheses:

1. On je *zadužen* za planiranje projekta. (He is responsible for project planning.)
2. *Zadužena* sam za nabavku materijala. (I am responsible for material procurement.)
3. Oni su *zaduženi* za čišćenje nakon događaja. (They are responsible for cleaning up after the event.)
4. *Zadužio* sam novac od prijatelja. (I borrowed money from a friend.)
5. Kompanija je *zadužena* za isporuku robe kupcu. (The company is responsible for delivering the goods to the customer.)
6. Banka mi je *zadužila* račun za kupovinu automobila. (The bank charged my account for the car purchase.)
7. Oni su *zaduženi* za obuku novih zaposlenih. (They are responsible for training new employees.)
8. Ova knjiga je *zadužena* u biblioteci. (This book is borrowed from the library.)
9. *Zaduženost* građana u Srbiji je visoka. (The indebtedness of citizens in Serbia is high.)
10. Ona je preuzela *zaduženje* za organizaciju događaja. (She took on the task of organizing the event.)